This paper deals with fair division of goods, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT) and algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves partitioning a set of goods, which can be modeled as a discrete structure, and hence, falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper proposes a constructive algorithm to solve the problem, which involves computational techniques and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The notion of fairness considered in the paper is related to economic theory and mechanism design, which are also subfields of computer science (cs.EC). Finally, the paper deals with optimization and approximation algorithms, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
